      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">23.107-4</ph> Products that contain, use, or are manufactured with ozone-depleting substances or products that contain or use high global warming potential hydrofluorocarbons.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Authorities.</i>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e17">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "/>Title VI of the Clean Air Act (<xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section7671&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42 U.S.C. 7671</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">et seq.</i>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e29">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Section 706 of Division D, title VII of the Omnibus Appropriations Act, 2009 (<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/plaw/111/public/8"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">Pub. L. 111-8</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e37">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> EPA regulations, Protection of Stratospheric Ozone (<xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/part-82"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">40 CFR part 82</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e45">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Program.</i> The EPA SNAP Program.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e52">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Agency program</i> s. Agencies shall implement cost-effective programs to minimize the procurement of materials and substances that contribute to the depletion of stratospheric ozone and/or result in the use, release, or emission of high global warming potential hydrofluorocarbons.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e59">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Procedures.</i> Agencies shall—</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e67">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Give preference to the procurement of acceptable alternative chemicals, products, and manufacturing processes that reduce overall risks to human health and the environment by minimizing—</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e73">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> The depletion of ozone in the upper atmosphere; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e78">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> The potential use, release, or emission of high global warming potential hydrofluorocarbons; and</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e83">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> In preparing specifications and purchase descriptions and in the acquisition of products and services—</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e89">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Comply with the requirements of title VI of the Clean Air Act; section 706 of division D, title VII of <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/plaw/111/public/8"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">Public Law 111-8</xref>; and <xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/section-82.84#p-82.84(a)(2)"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">40 CFR 82.84(a)(2)</xref> through<xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/section-82.84#p-82.84(a)(5)"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">(5)</xref>;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e103">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Substitute acceptable alternatives to ozone-depleting substances, as identified under <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section7671&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">42 U.S.C. 7671k</xref>, to the maximum extent practicable, as provided in <xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/section-82.84#p-82.84(a)(1)"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">40 CFR 82.84(a)(1)</xref>, except in the case of Class I substances being used for specified essential uses, as identified under <xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/section-82.4#p-82.4(n)"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">40 CFR 82.4(n)</xref>; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e117">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> Unless a particular contract requires otherwise, specify that, when feasible, contractors shall use another acceptable alternative in lieu of a high global warming potential hydrofluorocarbon in products and services in a particular end use for which EPA's SNAP program has identified other acceptable alternatives that have lower global warming potential.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1535e122">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Resource.</i> Refer to EPA's SNAP program website at <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                     <xref href="https://www.epa.gov/snap"
                           format="html"
                           scope="external"
                           class="- topic/xref ">https://www.epa.gov/​snap</xref>
                  </i> for the list of alternatives found at <xref href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-40/part-82/subpart-G"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">40 CFR part 82, subpart G</xref>, as well as supplemental tables of alternatives.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
